Package: tsreadex
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: tool for MPEG-TS stream selection and stabilization
 tsreadex reads an MPEG-TS stream (typically ARIB/Japanese broadcast
 transport streams) from a file or pipe and rewrites it: selecting a
 single service/program, remapping or dropping PIDs, completing or
 removing caption/superimpose streams, fixing up AAC audio tracks, and
 smoothing timing so that downstream encoders or streaming pipelines
 receive a stable feed. It is commonly used as a pre-processing filter
 in PVR setups such as EPGStation/Mirakurun.
